TITLE: Defining an Atomic Slot Recipe (sva) in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to define an atomic slot recipe for a checkbox component using the sva function. It includes base styles, variants, and default variants for multiple slots.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chakra-ui/panda/blob/main/website/pages/docs/concepts/slot-recipes.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { sva } from '../styled-system/css'

const checkbox = sva({
  slots: ['root', 'control', 'label'],
  base: {
    root: { display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: '2' },
    control: { borderWidth: '1px', borderRadius: 'sm' },
    label: { marginStart: '2' }
  },
  variants: {
    size: {
      sm: {
        control: { width: '8', height: '8' },
        label: { fontSize: 'sm' }
      },
      md: {
        control: { width: '10', height: '10' },
        label: { fontSize: 'md' }
      }
    }
  },
  defaultVariants: {
    size: 'sm'
  }
})
```

