TITLE: Merging CSS Objects with the css Function in Panda CSS
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to merge multiple style objects together using the css function. The later style objects override properties from earlier ones, as seen when style2's blue background overrides style1's red background.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chakra-ui/panda/blob/main/website/pages/docs/concepts/merging-styles.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import { css } from 'styled-system/css'

const style1 = {
  bg: 'red',
  color: 'white'
}

const style2 = {
  bg: 'blue'
}

const className = css(style1, style2) // => 'bg_blue text_white'
```

