TITLE: Merging Style Objects with CSS Function in React
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to use the updated `css` function to merge multiple style objects in React components. This approach is recommended over using the `cx` function for style merging.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chakra-ui/panda/blob/main/packages/generator/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-18_snippet_28

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { css, cx } from '../styled-system/css'

const App = () => {
  return (
    <>
-      <div className={cx(css({ mx: '3', paddingTop: '4' }), css({ mx: '10', pt: '6' }))}>  
+      <div className={css({ mx: '3', paddingTop: '4' }, { mx: '10', pt: '6' })}>
        Will result in `class="mx_10 pt_6"`
      </div>
    </>
  )
}
```

