TITLE: Static Expression Example with Variants
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use static expressions to generate style variants programmatically.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chakra-ui/panda/blob/main/website/pages/docs/guides/dynamic-styling.md#2025-04-18_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { cva } from '.panda/css'

const getVariants = () => {
  const spacingTokens = Object.entries({
    sm: 'token(spacing.1)',
    md: 'token(spacing.2)'
  })

  // Generate variants programmatically
  const variants = spacingTokens.map(([variant, token]) => [
    variant,
    { paddingX: token }
  ])
  return Object.fromEntries(variants)
}

const baseStyle = cva({
  variants: {
    variant: getVariants()
  }
})
```

