TITLE: Generating Atomic Styles with Panda CSS in JSX
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the css function from Panda to generate atomic styles. The function accepts a style object and returns a className string.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chakra-ui/panda/blob/main/website/pages/docs/concepts/writing-styles.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { css } from '../styled-system/css'

const styles = css({
  backgroundColor: 'gainsboro',
  borderRadius: '9999px',
  fontSize: '13px',
  padding: '10px 15px'
})

// Generated className:
// --> bg_gainsboro rounded_9999px fs_13px p_10px_15px

<div className={styles}>
  <p>Hello World</p>
</div>
```

