TITLE: Setting defaultValues in pattern configurations
DESCRIPTION: Example of defining a horizontal stack pattern with default values. This allows setting default gap or other properties for patterns.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chakra-ui/panda/blob/main/packages/core/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-18_snippet_59

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
defineConfig({
  patterns: {
    hstack: {
      properties: {
        justify: { type: 'property', value: 'justifyContent' },
        gap: { type: 'property', value: 'gap' },
      },
      // you can also use a token like '10'
      defaultValues: { gap: '40px' },
      transform(props) {
        const { justify, gap, ...rest } = props
        return {
          display: 'flex',
          alignItems: 'center',
          justifyContent: justify,
          gap,
          ...rest,
        }
      },
    },
  },
})
```

