TITLE: Strict Token Usage in Panda CSS Configuration
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use strictTokens and strictPropertyValues in Panda configuration to enforce token usage and valid CSS values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chakra-ui/panda/blob/main/website/pages/docs/concepts/writing-styles.md#2025-04-18_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
import { css } from '../styled-system/css'

css({ bg: 'red' }) // ‚ùå Error: "red" is not a valid token value
css({ fontSize: '123px' }) // ‚ùå Error: "123px" is not a valid token value

css({ bg: 'red.400' }) // ‚úÖ Valid
css({ fontSize: '[123px]' }) // ‚úÖ Valid, since `[123px]` is using the escape-hatch syntax
css({ content: 'abc' }) // ‚úÖ Valid, since `content` isn't bound to a config token
```

