TITLE: Correct Recipe-based Implementation in Panda CSS
DESCRIPTION: Shows the recommended approach using Panda's recipe system (cva) to handle dynamic styling with proper static extraction and type safety.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chakra-ui/panda/blob/main/website/pages/docs/guides/dynamic-styling.md#2025-04-18_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { useState } from 'react'
import { cva } from '../styled-system/cva'

const sectionRecipe = cva({
  base: { color: 'gray.100' },
  variants: {
    type: {
      primary: { color: 'red.300' },
      secondary: { color: 'blue.300' },
      tertiary: { color: 'green.300' }
    }
  }
})

const Section = () => {
  const [type, setType] = useState('primary')

  // ‚úÖ Good: This will work as expected
  return <section className={sectionRecipe({ type })}>‚úÖ With a recipe</section>
}
```

