TITLE: Configuring JSX Extraction in Panda
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to customize JSX extraction in Panda using 'matchTag' and 'matchTagProp' functions. This is useful for handling libraries with properties that look like CSS but should be ignored.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chakra-ui/panda/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-18_snippet_39

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export default defineConfig({
  // ...
  hooks: {
    'parser:before': ({ configure }) => {
      configure({
        // ignore the Select.Content entirely
        matchTag: (tag) => tag !== 'Select.Content',
        // ...or specifically ignore the `position` property
        matchTagProp: (tag, prop) => tag === 'Select.Content' && prop !== 'position',
      })
    },
  },
})
```

