TITLE: Adding New Conditions to Panda CSS
DESCRIPTION: This code block lists new conditions added to the Panda CSS preset base package, including their corresponding CSS selectors.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chakra-ui/panda/blob/main/packages/preset-base/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-18_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
- bb37d2b: Add support for new conditions

  - `current` -> `&:is([aria-current=true], [data-current])`
  - `today` -> `&[data-today]`
  - `unavailable` -> `&[data-unavailable]`
  - `rangeStart` -> `&[data-range-start]`
  - `rangeEnd` -> `&[data-range-end]`
  - `now` -> `&[data-now]`
  - `topmost` -> `&[data-topmost]`
  - `icon` -> `& :where(svg)`
  - `complete` -> `&[data-complete]`
  - `incomplete` -> `&[data-incomplete]`
  - `dragging` -> `&[data-dragging]`
  - `grabbed` -> `&[data-grabbed]`
  - `underValue` -> `&[data-state=under-value]`
  - `overValue` -> `&[data-state=over-value]`
  - `atValue` -> `&[data-state=at-value]`
  - `hidden` -> `&:is([hidden], [data-hidden])`
```

