TITLE: Incorrect Runtime Reference Implementation in Panda CSS
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates an anti-pattern where color values are referenced from an object at runtime, which won't be properly extracted by Panda's static analysis.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chakra-ui/panda/blob/main/website/pages/docs/guides/dynamic-styling.md#2025-04-18_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { useState } from 'react'
import { css } from '../styled-system/css'

const colorByType = {
  primary: 'red.300',
  secondary: 'blue.300',
  tertiary: 'green.300'
}

const Section = () => {
  const [type, setType] = useState('primary')

  // ‚ùå Avoid: since only "gray.100" is statically extractable here
  // This will not work as expected, the color CSS won't be generated
  return (
    <section className={css({ color: colorByType[type] ?? 'gray.100' })}>
      ‚ùå Will not be extracted
    </section>
  )
}
```

