TITLE: Configuring Custom Hash Function in Panda CSS
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to override the default toHash function used when config.hash is set to true in Panda CSS. It uses the utility:created hook to configure a custom hashing function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chakra-ui/panda/blob/main/packages/token-dictionary/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-18_snippet_30

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export default defineConfig({
  // ...
  hooks: {
    'utility:created': ({ configure }) => {
      configure({
        toHash: (paths, toHash) => {
          const stringConds = paths.join(':')
          const splitConds = stringConds.split('_')
          const hashConds = splitConds.map(toHash)
          return hashConds.join('_')
        },
      })
    },
  },
})
```

